list.item:
Whether or not to pursue the Administration’s plan to request from
                        Congress a similar amount of FMS financing
                        for Ethiopia in FY 78,

div.p:
—give only minimal compliance to EPMG requests
                    for cash sales of military equipment, tacitly encouraging it to go elsewhere for
                    its needs;

—be passive in the economic development field, letting the Ethiopians come to us
                    for assistance and providing it on our usual terms with no effort to meet their
                    special needs or wants;
